# GHLC Presentation Guidelines

Official sources: `docs/presentation/sources/GHLC_Presentation_Guidelines.pdf` and `docs/presentation/sources/2026 Student Speaker Series Slide Template A.pdf`

## Audience

Global health and science audience (GHLC Student Speaker Series). Assume no deep ML background. Every point must show clear relevance to global health.

## Mandatory Template and Slides

- Use the **2026 GHLC Student Speaker Series slide template** — copy to a folder you own before editing
- Required slide order: Title → Introduction → *(content)* → References → Acknowledgements → Thank You → Contact
- Title slide: presentation title, name, school/institution, **date of recording**
- Contact slide: email and LinkedIn only — **no social media**
- Cite all non-common-knowledge sources and **images/figures** on the References slide

## Time Budget — 8 Minutes or Less (Spoken)

| Section | Minutes |
|---------|---------|
| Title + self-introduction | ~1 |
| Background / introduction to topic | 2 |
| Body (project + evidence) | 2–3 |
| Conclusion (takeaways, call to action) | 2 |

References, Acknowledgements, and Contact are mandatory deck slides; they follow the spoken 8 minutes.

## Self-Introduction Must Include

- Grade, hometown/region, school
- Extracurricular activities
- Interests and future plans (professional bio)

## Tone

- Lead with the central question: Can AI expand access to diagnostic healthcare?
- Use accessible language: "pattern recognition on X-ray images" not layer-by-layer CNN details.
- Connect every technical point back to healthcare access and equity.
- Verify facts and statistics with reputable sources before recording.

## Required Content

- Clear global health relevance in background
- For own work: explain what you did with supporting evidence and figures
- Limitations: dataset bias, FP/FN, validation gaps
- Responsible AI: who gets access, validation, disparity risks
- Personal reflection and call to action or thought-provoking question
- Extension preview: deployment in low-resource settings

## Recording and Submission

- Pre-recorded Zoom video; **camera and audio on** at all times
- Formal attire; professional background; minimal noise
- Deadline: **July 20, 2026, 11:59 PM Eastern**
- Google Drive folder: `LastName_FirstName_TITLE_OF_PRESENTATION` with editor-access link
- Form: https://forms.gle/Wx7L1WS59DECbtAV8

## Prohibited

- Claiming the model replaces doctors or provides diagnoses
- Jargon without plain-language explanation
- Social media on the contact slide
- Exceeding 8 minutes without cutting imaging overview first
- Removing References, Acknowledgements, or Contact slides
